---
description: Prohibit agents from creating Git commits in this project
alwaysApply: true
---

# No Agent-Created Git Commits

- Never create, amend, squash, rebase, tag, or push a Git commit.
- Do not run `git add` unless the user explicitly requests staging only.
- Use read-only Git commands for inspection and leave implementation changes uncommitted.
- If asked to commit, explain that this project rule prohibits agent-created commits.
